.c1 "The .den archive format"
.lp
Agar stores multimedia data in
.Xr den 5
archives.
Agar's build system compiles files in various formats into an archive file
(with the
.Pa den
suffix), using the
.Xr dencomp 1
utility.
.c2 "Typical Makefile for a .den archive"
.lp
A typical
.Pa Makefile
for a \fIden\fP archive may look like the following.
The
.Xr dencomp 1
utility may also be invoked manually.
As the
.Xr den 5
archive format was designed to allow language-specific overrides, each
archive entry includes an optional ISO 639 language code.
In addition to
.Xr dencomp 1 ,
the Agar distribution comes with an utility to extract archive members,
.Xr denex 1 .
.sp
.Bd -code "Typical Makefile for a .den archive"
DEN=		dark-castle.den
DEN_DIR=	cave/dark-castle
DEN_NAME=	"The Dark Castle in the Deep Forest"
DEN_AUTHOR=	"Rodrigue"
DEN_COPYRIGHT=	"2004 Rodrigue"

OGG=	castle-music.ogg
WAV=	castle-sounds.wav
XCF=	castle.xcf \\
	briques.xcf
MPEG=	castle-intro.mpeg

include ${TOP}/mk/csoft.den.mk
.Ed
.Bd -code "Applying language override to den archive members"
$ dencomp -o dark-castle.ogg -n 'The Dark Castle in the Deep Forest' \\
    castle-music.ogg \\
    castle-sounds-en.wav:en \\
    castle-sounds-fr.wav:fr \\
    castle-intro-en.mpeg:en \\
    castle-intro-fr.mpeg:fr
.Ed
.c2 "Recognized file formats"
.lp
Agar currently recognizes the following file formats:
.Bd -fig "Recognized file formats"
.TS
